# Blog content CRUD

## Create post

1. File: `src/content/blog/YYYY-MM-DD-slug.mdx` (always `.mdx` for new posts)
2. Frontmatter minimum:

```yaml
---
title: "Title"
description: "SEO / card summary"
tags: [ai, tutorial]
# optional: icon, accent_color, date, ads, toc, related, image
---
```

3. Body: Markdown/MDX. Remapped components via `RenderMDX.astro`: `Pintora`, `AlertInfo`, `PostLink`, `Picture`, etc.
4. Series (optional): add post id `/blog/YYYY/MM/DD/slug` (**no** `.html`) to `src/data/series/<series>.ts` and ensure key is in `SERIES_CONFIG` (`src/data/series.ts`)
5. Related posts: `related: [other-entry-id]` using content collection ids

## URL rules

- Filename may use single-digit M/D; URLs are **zero-padded** via `postUrlFromId()`
- Shape: `/blog/YYYY/MM/DD/slug.html` — do not break this helper

## Update / delete

- Edit MDX frontmatter/body in place
- Remove from series maps when deleting
- Tags pages regenerate from frontmatter at build

## Do not

- Do not invent Jekyll `_posts` paths; content lives in `src/content/blog/`
- Do not put tool logic inside blog MDX except demo widgets under `src/components/blog/`
